A) Highlight high scores (≥ 85)
=================================

Excel

Select the Score column (E:E or the score cells in your table).

Home → Conditional Formatting → Highlight Cells Rules → Greater Than…

Enter 85 → choose a format → OK.

Google Sheets

Select Score cells.

Format → Conditional formatting.

Format rules: Greater than or equal to → 85 → choose a style → Done.


B) Color scale by Score
===========================

Excel: Home → Conditional Formatting → Color Scales → choose a 3-color scale.

Sheets: In the conditional format sidebar, pick Color scale tab → choose a 3-color scale.

C) Flag duplicate Names
=========================


Excel: Select Name column → Home → Conditional Formatting → Highlight Cells Rules → Duplicate Values…
